    "discriminators": [
     "A held, driven flow: level and LOUD where AIR-HISS is a quiet leak. Against AIR-HISS the separation is three-fold and independent — LEVEL (root_mean_square_level ~0.16 vs ~0.03), BRIGHTNESS (spectral_centroid_hz ~2.2 kHz vs ~5.5 kHz; zero_crossings_per_second ~2500 vs ~7000), and DURATION (seconds, not tens of seconds).",
     "Sustained where AIR-BURST is impulsive: envelope_temporal_centroid ~0.48 with a plateau, crest_factor ~4 not ~9, and envelope_attack_seconds in tens of milliseconds, not single milliseconds.",
     "Symmetric/front-loaded where AIR-SUCTION is back-loaded: envelope_skewness is mildly POSITIVE here and negative for SUCTION, and SUCTION's envelope_temporal_centroid gate (>= 0.40, expected ~0.63) is the real boundary."
    ],
