    "discriminators": [
     "The one AIR subcategory defined by envelope DIRECTION rather than by spectrum. Air drawn INWARD swells: the energy arrives late, so envelope_temporal_centroid runs ~0.63 (gated at 0.40 minimum) against ~0.48 for AIR-BLOW and ~0.25 for AIR-BURST, and envelope_skewness goes NEGATIVE (~-0.6) where every outward air event is positive. The attack is slow (envelope_attack_seconds ~0.35 s) and the release is abrupt — a decay run backwards.",
     "Spectrally it is nearly a twin of AIR-BLOW: same flatness, same centroid, same level, same noise morphology. Do NOT try to separate them on timbre — that comparison carries no information. The entire discrimination lives in four envelope features (envelope_temporal_centroid, envelope_skewness, envelope_attack_seconds, envelope_release_seconds) plus a POSITIVE spectral_centroid_slope_hz_per_second as the intake accelerates and the flow gets brighter.",
     "Not AIR-HISS: far shorter, roughly four times louder, and non-stationary.",
     "Not AIR-BURST: the crest_factor ceiling of 12 and the envelope_temporal_centroid floor of 0.40 both exclude a front-loaded transient."
    ],
